<main id="content" class="content"> <header> <h1 class="title">Twenty-First Sunday After Pentecost</h1>
 <p class="subtitle" role="doc-subtitle">Jan 13, 2015 00:00</p>
</header> <p>
Lord,
</p>

 <p>
Stay with me <br></br>
for a moment <br></br>
while I divide <br></br>
up my life.
</p>

 <p>
I’ll give you Sunday, <br></br>
but I’m keeping <br></br>
Monday through Saturday.
</p>

 <p>
I’ll give you ten percent, <br></br>
so long as you don’t <br></br>
ask what I do with <br></br>
the other ninety.
</p>

 <p>
I’ll do whatever you ask, <br></br>
just don’t make any <br></br>
unreasonable demands.
</p>

 <p>
Then, in the stillness, <br></br>
I hear a quiet voice <br></br>
whisper the question <br></br>
I’m afraid to answer:
</p>

 <p>
“Why do you call me ‘Lord?’”
</p>

 <p>
Lord, have mercy.
</p>

 <p>
 <i>Amen</i>
</p>




